440
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:07,000
WHOSE PRINTS ARE ON THAT SAFE?
STARTING WITH THE HUSBAND.

441
00:23:09,100 --> 00:23:10,900
OK, MAYBE THREE
IS A BETTER BET.

442
00:23:10,900 --> 00:23:12,200
WHY DO WE NEED A VOTE?

443
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:13,700
WHY CAN'T WE JUST
HAVE IT CHECKED OUT?

444
00:23:13,700 --> 00:23:15,200
BECAUSE MR. MARKS
WILL NEVER ALLOW IT.

445
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:17,500
WELL, THEN MAYBE THAT
TELLS US SOMETHING, TOO.

446
00:23:17,700 --> 00:23:19,000
NO.

447
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:22,600
LIKE I TOLD YOU BEFORE,
THERE WAS NO ROBBERY.

448
00:23:22,700 --> 00:23:24,300
NOW WHAT IS THIS ABOUT?

449
00:23:26,500 --> 00:23:28,300
I HAVE A GIFT.

450
00:23:28,800 --> 00:23:31,000
I CAN SEE GHOSTS, AND...

451
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:33,900
THE OTHER DAY,
YOUR WIFE'S SPIRIT WAS WITH ME.

452
00:23:33,900 --> 00:23:35,100
THAT'S RIDICULOUS.

453
00:23:35,100 --> 00:23:37,900
SHE GAVE ME A VISION ABOUT WHAT
HAPPENED THE NIGHT THAT SHE DIED,

454
00:23:37,900 --> 00:23:40,100
AND IT LOOKED LIKE SHE HAD
WALKED IN ON A ROBBERY.

455
00:23:40,100 --> 00:23:42,600
WHICH IS ODD, CONSIDERING
YOU SAID THERE WASN'T ONE.

456
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:45,400
I THINK IT'S TIME
FOR YOU BOTH TO LEAVE.

457
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:48,200
THE SAFE BEHIND
THAT PICTURE FRAME,

458
00:23:48,400 --> 00:23:49,900
IT HAD BEEN RUMMAGED.

459
00:23:49,900 --> 00:23:54,200
AND SHE WAS EITHER HIT OR TRIPPED
OR FELL SOMEWHERE OVER THERE.

460
00:23:56,100 --> 00:23:58,700
THAT INFORMATION
WASN'T IN ANY OF THE NEWSPAPERS.

461
00:23:58,700 --> 00:24:00,900
SOMETIMES SPIRITS
STAY EARTH-BOUND.

462
00:24:01,100 --> 00:24:02,300
IT'S USUALLY
FOR A REASON.

463
00:24:02,300 --> 00:24:04,000
I THINK THAT SHE'S
PROTECTING SOMEONE...

464
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:07,200
TIM, KRISTY, OR...
MAYBE EVEN YOU.

465
00:24:07,900 --> 00:24:09,500
AND WHAT WOULD SHE HAVE
TO PROTECT ME FROM?

466
00:24:09,500 --> 00:24:10,500
SHE DIDN'T TELL ME,

467
00:24:10,500 --> 00:24:12,700
BUT I THINK IT'S SOMETHING
THAT SHE WAS ASHAMED OF.

468
00:24:12,900 --> 00:24:14,500
MELINDA SPOKE
WITH TIM'S ROOMMATE.

469
00:24:14,500 --> 00:24:17,300
HE SAID YOU'D BEEN THERE LOOKING
FOR TIM BEFORE YOUR WIFE DIED.

470
00:24:17,300 --> 00:24:20,700
HE WAS WORRIED THAT YOU THOUGHT
MAYBE THEY HAD HAD AN AFFAIR.

471
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:23,400
OK, THIS IS NONE
OF YOUR BUSINESS.

472
00:24:23,700 --> 00:24:27,700
UNLESS YOU HAVE SOME REASON FOR
WANTING MY WIFE'S MEMORY TARNISHED.

473
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:30,100
ACTUALLY, WE THINK
IT'S YOUR STERLING EPUTATION

474
00:24:30,100 --> 00:24:32,100
YOUR WIFE IS TRYING
TO KEEP UNTARNISHED.

475
00:24:32,100 --> 00:24:34,000
YOU KEEP SAYING
THERE WASN'T A FIRE,

476
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:36,700
BUT I SEE ASHES;
SOMETHING BURNING.

477
00:24:36,700 --> 00:24:38,100
WAS THERE ANYTHING
MISSING FROM THE SAFE,

478
00:24:38,100 --> 00:24:39,900
ANYTHING AT ALL THAT
COULD HAVE BEEN BURNED?

479
00:24:39,900 --> 00:24:41,800
I HAVEN'T HAD THE HEART
TO OPEN IT SINCE SHE DIED.

480
00:24:41,800 --> 00:24:43,800
I'VE BEEN AFRAID
OF WHAT I MIGHT FIND.

481
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:46,500
LIKE EVIDENCE OF AN AFFAIR?

482
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:48,900
NONE OF IT MATTERS NOW.

483
00:24:49,600 --> 00:24:51,200
I LOVED MY WIFE,

484
00:24:51,300 --> 00:24:53,500
AND IF TIM HAD SOMETNG
TO DO WITH HER DEATH,

485
00:24:53,500 --> 00:24:55,500
THEN YES,
I WANT TO KNOW ABOUT IT.

486
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:59,300
BUT IT'S NONE OF YOUR CONCERN,
SO IF YOU'LL PLEASE EXCUSE ME...

487
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:26,800
SO THE BURNING PAPER IN YOUR VISION,
ANY IDEA WHAT IT WAS?

488
00:25:26,800 --> 00:25:27,900
IT WAS CHARRED, 

489
00:25:27,900 --> 00:25:30,500
BUT I COULD MAKE OUT THAT IT WAS
A WOMAN'S HANDWRITING, SO...

490
00:25:30,500 --> 00:25:32,500
SEE? CAN I CALL IT OR WHAT!

491
00:25:32,500 --> 00:25:34,200
A LOVE LETTER.
IT'S GOTTA BE.

492
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:35,600
THE GHOST COULD HAVE BEEN
BURNING IT.

493
00:25:35,900 --> 00:25:38,900
TIM WALKED IN,
THEY FOUGHT, AND KABONK!

494
00:25:38,900 --> 00:25:41,800
OR TIM COULD HAVE BEEN BURNING IT
WHEN MRS. MARKS WALKED IN.

495
00:25:41,800 --> 00:25:42,900
OR MR. MARKS BURNED IT.

496
00:25:42,900 --> 00:25:45,400
WELL, ANY WAY YOU SLICE IT,
THE PAPER WAS BURNED.

497
00:25:45,400 --> 00:25:48,600
SO SOMEONE WANTED WHATEVER WAS
ON IT TO BE KEPT A SECRET.

498
00:25:48,600 --> 00:25:50,400
YEAH, AND THE GHOST
STILL DOES.

499
00:25:50,600 --> 00:25:52,300
OOH, I'LL GET IT.

500
00:25:52,700 --> 00:25:54,000
MAYBE SAM IS EARLY.

501
00:25:54,900 --> 00:25:55,800
KRISTY!

502
00:25:57,000 --> 00:25:58,100
WHAT'S WRONG?

503
00:25:58,600 --> 00:26:01,000
- HOW COULD YOU DO THIS?
- DO WHAT?

504
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:05,400
THE COPS JUST TOOK TIM IN FOR QUESTIONING
ABOUT SOME SUPPOSED ROBBERY AT MY HOUSE!

505
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:09,200
MY DAD HAD THE SAFE FINGERPRINTED
BECAUSE OF WHAT YOU SAID!

506
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:11,100
WELL, IF HIS FINGERPRINTS
WERE THERE...

507
00:26:11,100 --> 00:26:12,800
OF COURSE THEY WERE THERE!

508
00:26:12,800 --> 00:26:14,300
HE WAS MY MOM'S ASSISTANT!

509
00:26:14,300 --> 00:26:15,600
KRISTY,
I KNOW THAT YOU'RE UPSET,

510
00:26:15,600 --> 00:26:18,000
BUT MAYBE YOUR FEELINGS
FOR TIM ARE CLOUDING YOUR JUDGMENT.

511
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:19,300
HE'S INNOCENT!

512
00:26:19,500 --> 00:26:21,700
HE WAS WITH ME,
WE WERE AT THE BOOKSTORE.

513
00:26:21,900 --> 00:26:23,500
- DID YOU TELL YOUR DAD THAT?
- YEAH.

514
00:26:23,500 --> 00:26:26,800
MY DAD THINKS THAT
I'M JUST LYING TO PROTECT TIM,

515
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:28,500
AND HE WON'T EVEN
LOOKT ME.

516
00:26:28,500 --> 00:26:33,100
LIKE I WOULD PROTECT MY OWN
MOM'S MURDERER, THAT'S INSANE!

517
00:26:34,300 --> 00:26:37,400
LOOK, YOU KNOW THAT HE HAS A HISTORY
AND A CRIMINAL RECORD,

518
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:40,200
AND MAYBE IT'S POSSIBLE
THAT HE ISN'T WHO YOU THINK HE IS.

519
00:26:40,200 --> 00:26:42,900
I KNOW THAT HE WOULD
NOT HURT ANYONE.

520
00:26:43,700 --> 00:26:46,500
AND IF YOU DO TALK TO
GHOSTS LIKE MY DAD SAID,

521
00:26:46,500 --> 00:26:48,500
WHY DON'T YOU
JUST ASK MY MOM?

522
00:26:48,500 --> 00:26:50,400
BECAUSE I DON'T THINK
SHE'D TALK TO ME.

523
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:54,800
SHE'S MAD BECAUSE I DIDN'T
KEEP YOU AND TIM APART.

524
00:26:54,800 --> 00:26:55,700
WHAT?!

525
00:26:56,100 --> 00:26:58,300
SOMETIMES I JUST HATE HER.

526
00:27:02,900 --> 00:27:04,200
THIS ISN'T WHAT I WANTED.

527
00:27:04,200 --> 00:27:05,600
THEN WHAT DO YOU WANT?

528
00:27:06,200 --> 00:27:07,900
PLEASE, JUST TELL ME
WHAT HAPPENED,

529
00:27:07,900 --> 00:27:10,200
BECAUSE YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
WHO CAN FIX THIS.

530
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:12,000
I REALLY WISH I COULD.

531
00:27:13,300 --> 00:27:15,800
BUT SOME SECRETS
ARE BETTER LEFT ALONE.

532
00:27:21,200 --> 00:27:23,300
I GOT NOTHIN'.
TIM'S STILL BEING QUESTIONED.

533
00:27:23,300 --> 00:27:24,800
DETECTIVE BLAIR COULDN'T
TELL ME ANYTHING YET.

534
00:27:24,800 --> 00:27:27,000
WELL, DID THEY FIND ANYTHING
MISSING FROM THE SAFE?

535
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:28,500
WHAT PART OF "I GOT NOTHIN'"
DIDN'T YOU GET?

536
00:27:28,500 --> 00:27:30,900
ALL RIGHT. SORRY, I THOUGHT
YOU COULD PULL SOME WEIGHT IN THERE.

537
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:33,000
NO, BUT APPARENTLY
JUDGE MARKS DOES.

538
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:34,700
THEY'RE LOOKING AT THIS
AS A POSSIBLE MURDER CASE.

539
00:27:34,700 --> 00:27:36,700
MY GUESS IS, TIM'S GOING TO
BE IN THERE FOR A WHILE.

540
00:27:36,700 --> 00:27:39,300
OH, I HOPE I DID THE RIGHT THING
BY HAVING THEM CHECK THAT SAFE.

541
00:27:39,300 --> 00:27:40,900
DON'T BE SUCH A SOFTIE.

542
00:27:40,900 --> 00:27:44,400
YOU TOLD ME YOURSELF YOU HAD A VISION
OF MRS. MARKS WALKING IN ON A BREAK-IN.

543
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:46,700
TIM'S PRINTS ARE
ALL OVER THAT SAFE,

544
00:27:46,700 --> 00:27:48,300
OK? HE SEEMS
PRETTY GUILTY TO ME.

545
00:27:48,300 --> 00:27:48,900
YEAH, BUT...

546
00:27:48,900 --> 00:27:50,700
AND PLEASE DON'T TELL ME
YOU'RE HAVING SECOND THOUGHTS

547
00:27:50,700 --> 00:27:53,300
BECAUSE DEBORAH NEVER ACTUALLY
SAID SHE SAW TIM DO IT.

548
00:27:53,300 --> 00:27:54,900
WE BOTH KNOW SHE JUST
SAYING WHAT SHE DID.

549
00:27:54,900 --> 00:27:56,700
OK, STILL...
AND I DON'T WANT TO HEAR

550
00:27:56,700 --> 00:27:59,700
PLEAS THAT KRISTY SAID
SHE SWEARS HE WAS WITH HER.

551
00:27:59,700 --> 00:28:01,000
SHE'S NO MORE RELIABLE
THAN HER MOTHER.

552
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:01,600
EXCEPT...

553
00:28:01,600 --> 00:28:03,000
DON'T TELL ME
YOU'RE FALLING FOR TIM, TOO.

554
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:05,700
NO! ALL RIGHT?
I'M JUST TRYING TO THINK OUT LOUD,

555
00:28:05,700 --> 00:28:08,000
WHICH WOULD BE EASIER
WITHOUT SO MANY INTERRUPTIONS.

556
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:08,800
SORRY.

557
00:28:09,100 --> 00:28:11,100
THE GHOST SAID THAT KRISTY
DOESN'T KNOW WHO TIM IS,

558
00:28:11,100 --> 00:28:12,800
SO COULDN'T THAT HAVE SOMETHING
TO DO WITH HIS RECORD?

559
00:28:12,800 --> 00:28:14,100
I MEAN, MAYBE
THAT'S WHAT SHE BURNED.

560
00:28:14,100 --> 00:28:16,000
- THE POLICE REPORT, OR...
- WHICH WE CAN'T ACCESS.

561
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:17,700
YEAH, BUT WE COULD TALK
TO SOMEBODY WHO KNEW HIM,

562
00:28:17,700 --> 00:28:20,300
HIS MOM ONLY LIVES LIKE
AN HOUR AWAY... CRAP!

563
00:28:20,800 --> 00:28:23,200
MY DATE WITH SAM!
I ALMOST FORGOT.

564
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:25,000
I KNEW YOU DIDN'T
WEAR THAT FOR ME.

565
00:28:26,200 --> 00:28:27,400
I CAN'T CANCEL, OK?

566
00:28:27,400 --> 00:28:28,700
- CAN YOU HANDLE THIS?
- I'D LOVE TO,

567
00:28:28,700 --> 00:28:30,900
BUT STARTING AT 3:00,
I GOT BACK-TO-BACK CASES.

568
00:28:30,900 --> 00:28:33,100
FINE. YOU KNOW WHAT,
IF I RUSH, I'LL MAKE ITBACK IN TIME.

569
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:38,600
I ONLY FOUND OUT MY SON WAS IN TROUBLE
AGAIN WHEN I CALLED HIS APARTMENT.

570
00:28:38,600 --> 00:28:40,800
TIM DIDN'T WANT ME
TO BE UPSET, I GUESS.

571
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:42,600
YOU'RE A FRIEND
OF MRS. MARKS?

572
00:28:42,600 --> 00:28:43,700
YES.

573
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:46,300
SHE THOUGHT A LOT OF YOUR SON.
THAT'S WHY I'M HERE.

574
00:28:46,500 --> 00:28:47,400
YEAH.

575
00:28:47,700 --> 00:28:50,900
SHE WAS A WONDERFUL PERSON,
REALLY BELIEVED IN TIM.

576
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:53,300
HE'S A GOOD BOY.

577
00:28:53,300 --> 00:28:55,800
THERE'S NO WAY HE HAD ANYTHING
TO DO WITH HER DEATH.

578
00:28:57,000 --> 00:28:59,600
BUT HE WAS ARRESTED
BEFORE FOR ROBBERY.

579
00:28:59,600 --> 00:29:01,000
HE WAS INNOCENT THEN, TOO.

580
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:03,600
TIM'S GIRLFRIEND'S
OLDER BROTHER DID IT.

581
00:29:03,700 --> 00:29:05,500
SO WHY DID TIM TAKE THE BLAME?

582
00:29:06,500 --> 00:29:08,300
THE GIRL CAME TO HIM CRYING,

583
00:29:08,300 --> 00:29:10,800
SAID THAT HER BROTHER
BROKE INTO AN ELECTRONICS STORE.

584
00:29:10,800 --> 00:29:13,400
TIM WENT TO STOP HIM,
ONLY THE COPS SHOWED UP.

585
00:29:13,400 --> 00:29:15,700
HE KNEW THE OLDER BOY
HAD 2 STRIKES,

586
00:29:15,700 --> 00:29:17,200
SO HE SAID HE DID IT.

587
00:29:18,200 --> 00:29:21,900
DO YOU MIND IF LOOK AT SOME
OF HIS THINGS? IT MIGHT HELP.

588
00:29:21,900 --> 00:29:24,000
YOU CAN SCOUR THE WHOLE HOUSE
IF YOU LIKE.

589
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:26,000
I JUST WANT MY BOY'S
NAME CLEARED.

590
00:29:28,500 --> 00:29:30,200
THAT'S TIM AND HIS
BROTHER GEORGE.

591
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:32,600
- OLDER?
- MMM, BY ABOUT 8 YEARS.

592
00:29:32,700 --> 00:29:34,800
TIM WAS AN UNEXPECTED BLESSING.

593
00:29:40,800 --> 00:29:42,100
<i>THE LITTLE PRINCE.</i>

594
00:29:42,400 --> 00:29:44,400
THAT WAS TIM'S FIRST BOOK.

595
00:29:50,800 --> 00:29:52,500
THERE'S A PAGE MISSING.

596
00:29:52,800 --> 00:29:54,300
DO YOU KNOW WHAT HAPPENED?

597
00:29:54,400 --> 00:29:55,300
GOD KNOWS.

598
00:29:55,300 --> 00:29:58,000
IT'S A WONDER THIS THING
HAS ANY PAGES LEFT AT ALL.

599
00:29:58,200 --> 00:29:59,700
TIM JUST LOVED
THAT STORY.

600
00:29:59,700 --> 00:30:01,700
IT CAME HOME
FROM THE HOSPITAL WITH HIM.

601
00:30:01,900 --> 00:30:03,100
WELL, THAT'S SWEET.

602
00:30:03,100 --> 00:30:04,900
USUALLY IT'S BLANKETS
AND BOOTIES.

603
00:30:05,300 --> 00:30:07,300
I'M AFRAID THEY WOULDN'T
HAVE FIT OUR TIMMY.

604
00:30:07,300 --> 00:30:09,700
HE WAS ALMOST 6 MONTHS OLD
WHEN WE BROUGHT HIM HOME.

605
00:30:09,900 --> 00:30:10,900
WHY? WAS SOMETHING WRONG?

606
00:30:10,900 --> 00:30:12,800
NO, IT WAS JUST
THE AGENCY PROTOCOL.

607
00:30:14,300 --> 00:30:15,800
TIM WAS ADOPTED.

608
00:30:27,700 --> 00:30:29,500
I RUINED EVERYTHING.

609
00:30:29,900 --> 00:30:31,200
IT'S OK.

610
00:30:31,700 --> 00:30:33,800
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO KEEP SECRETS ANYMORE.

611
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:36,200
I KNOW WHY YOU CARE
SO MUCH ABOUT TIM,

612
00:30:36,700 --> 00:30:39,300
AND I KNOW WHY YOU DON'T WANT
HIM TO BE WITH YOUR DAUGHTER.

613
00:30:41,500 --> 00:30:43,500
HE'S HER BROTHER,
ISN'T HE?

614
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:47,300
YES.

615
00:30:49,300 --> 00:30:51,100
TIM'S MY SON.

616
00:30:52,400 --> 00:30:55,100
IT WAS THE HARDEST THING
I EVER DID,LETTING HIM GO.

617
00:30:56,100 --> 00:30:59,100
AND THEN WHEN I FOUND HIM AGAIN,
IT WAS LIKE A GIFT.

618
00:30:59,500 --> 00:31:01,100
TELL ME WHAT HAPPENED.

619
00:31:02,400 --> 00:31:05,400
DOUGLAS AND I FELL IN LOVE
WHEN HE WAS IN LAW SCHOOL.

620
00:31:05,400 --> 00:31:06,600
I WAS AN UNDERGRAD.

621
00:31:07,100 --> 00:31:09,800
NOT LONG AFTER THAT,
I FOUND OUT THAT I WAS PREGNANT.

622
00:31:10,000 --> 00:31:11,600
AND HE DIDN'T
WANT CHILDREN YET?

623
00:31:11,600 --> 00:31:13,000
IT WASN'T HIS.

624
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:15,200
IT WAS SOMEBODY
I DATED BEFORE HIM.

625
00:31:15,200 --> 00:31:17,400
SO I TOLD DOUG
THAT I WAS TAKING A YEAR ABROAD,

626
00:31:17,400 --> 00:31:19,000
AND I WENT HOME
TO HAVE THE BABY.

627
00:31:20,300 --> 00:31:23,400
I TRIED TO KEEP HIM,
BUT I WAS 18,

628
00:31:23,400 --> 00:31:25,200
BARELY OLDER THAN KRISTY.

629
00:31:25,500 --> 00:31:28,300
IN THE END, I HAD TO DO
WHAT WAS BEST FOR MY BABY.

630
00:31:28,500 --> 00:31:30,300
AND YOU NEVER TOLD DOUGLAS?

631
00:31:30,600 --> 00:31:32,500
I TRIED TO PUT IT BEHIND ME,

632
00:31:32,800 --> 00:31:35,400
BUT IT HAUNTED ME.

633
00:31:36,200 --> 00:31:39,300
I LOOKED FOR TIM IN THE
FACE OF EVERY BOY HIS AGE.

634
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:42,800
AND FINALLY I HIRED
A PRIVATE DETECTIVE.

635
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:44,600
AND HE FOUND TIM IN JAIL.

636
00:31:44,600 --> 00:31:47,800
I COULDN'T STAND SEEING
MY BOY IN THAT PLACE.

637
00:31:47,900 --> 00:31:49,600
I HAD TO GET HIM OUT.

638
00:31:49,600 --> 00:31:51,500
SO WHY DIDN'T YOU
TELL YOUR FAMILY?

639
00:31:51,500 --> 00:31:52,500
OR HIS?

640
00:31:52,500 --> 00:31:56,000
I THOUGHT MAYBE THERE WAS A WAY I COULD
HELP HIM WITHOUT STIRRING THINGS UP.

641
00:31:58,100 --> 00:32:00,300
AND THEN KRISTY FELL FOR TIM.

642
00:32:01,300 --> 00:32:03,800
SEEMS LIKE THAT WOULD HAVE
BEEN A GOOD TIME TO SAY SOMETHING.

643
00:32:03,800 --> 00:32:07,000
AND I WOULD HAVE IF IT WEREN'T FOR
DOUGLAS' APPOINTMENT TO THE BENCH.

644
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:08,900
SO I FIGURED I WOULD JUST KEEP
TIM AND KRISTY APART

645
00:32:08,900 --> 00:32:12,200
UNTIL HE WAS CONFIRMED,
AND THEN I'D TELL EVERYONE.

646
00:32:12,200 --> 00:32:15,100
SO THE BUSINESS TRIP,
WITH TIM,

647
00:32:15,100 --> 00:32:17,800
THAT WAS REALLY JUST TO
SPEND TIME WITH YOUR CHILD?

648
00:32:18,200 --> 00:32:19,200
YES.

649
00:32:20,300 --> 00:32:21,700
AND THEN A WEEK LATER,

650
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:25,600
I LOST THE CHANCE
OF EVER TELLING HIM THE TRUTH.

651
00:32:28,300 --> 00:32:30,600
I'D STOPPED BY THE HOUSE
TO GET MY CELL PHONE.

652
00:32:31,200 --> 00:32:32,800
I COULDN'T HELP
BUT THINK IT WAS TIM.

653
00:32:32,800 --> 00:32:35,300
MAYBE HE WAS GETTING
BACK AT ME ABOUT KRISTY.

654
00:32:39,600 --> 00:32:43,800
AND THEN I SAW THAT THE NOTE I WROTE HIM
WHEN HE WAS A BABY WAS GONE.

655
00:32:44,100 --> 00:32:45,300
I PANICKED.

